      "message": "Disclosure: this change was developed with the assistance of an AI coding agent (Claude), under my direction, review, and steering throughout. I have reviewed the design and the code and stand behind the contribution; the ECA applies as usual.\n\nScope: this implements partial-clone support for blobless clones (--filter\u003dblob:none) and blob:limit. It covers on-demand lazy fetching of missing blobs (so blame/checkout/diff work on a blobless clone), partial-clone config persistence (remote.\u003cname\u003e.promisor, partialclonefilter, extensions.partialClone), .promisor pack markers, GC safety on partial clones, batched prefetch during checkout, and a --filter option for the pgm clone command.\n\nNot yet supported (planned follow-up): treeless clones (--filter\u003dtree:0). Those additionally require (a) honoring explicit wants in PackWriter\u0027s tree-depth filter (depthSkip), and (b) relaxing the post-fetch connectivity check for partial clones. The DFS object store is also out of scope here (file-based object store only).",
